OL,3,CTram and rail passengers face a week
OL,4,Cof disruption as strikes get underway
OL,6,FThe Rail Delivery Group (RDG), which
OL,7,Frepresents train operators, wrote to
OL,8,FAslef last week suggesting informal
OL,9,Ftalks which could result in more
OL,10,Fformal negotiations.
OL,12,FA spokesman for the RDG said the rail
OL,13,Findustry is "working hard to keep
OL,14,Ftrains running" but "it is likely that
OL,15,Fservices on some lines will be
OL,16,Faffected on the evening before and
OL,17,Fmorning after each strike between May
OL,18,F7 and May 9" as trains will not be in
OL,19,Fthe right depots to start services the
OL,20,Ffollowing day.
